summary: Hello! I am thinking of applying to be a writer for the zine, but I saw it says works submitted for the application should be up...
question: Hello! I am thinking of applying to be a writer for the zine, but I saw it says works submitted for the application should be up to 15,000 words. Does that mean we have to submit about 15k of words, or that the samples combined can't be more than 15k words?
answer:
We’re happy to have caught your interest! As stated in our application form, your samples must be anywhere from 1k to 15k words combined, meaning the latter is indeed the maximum count we’ll be taking in, although if extrapolated by a few hundred words or so it won’t serve to disqualify you.

What’s really important is that we’ll be only taking finished pieces into consideration - that’s to say, only finished stories, multi-chaptered or not - so our mod team is able to access your ability to make a narrative come full circle.

✘

summary: Last weekend’s Times had reviews of Big Little Lies, Killing Eve + The Handmaid’s Tale as well as the new book about Chateau...
body:
Last weekend’s Times had reviews of Big Little Lies, Killing Eve + The Handmaid’s Tale as well as the new book about Chateau Marmont. They also had Caitlin Moran writing about Glastonbury + an interview w/Lauren Laverne (I wish she’d write her memoirs) 

And last week’s Stylist had Lily Allen interviewing Jodie Comer.
